2010-06-05  Paul Fitzpatrick  <paulfitz@alum.mit.edu>

	* scripts/fetch-ace.sh: Change ACE configuration when bundled
	with YARP to facilitate compiling YARP with gcc (as opposed
	to g++).  The core yarp libraries and executables make
	no use of C++ libraries, and so can be compiled without 
	linking to libstdc++.  This can be handy for avoiding conflicts
	with different versions of this library.  Steps:
	  cd $YARP_ROOT
	  mkdir -p build/no_cxx_lib
	  cd build/no_cxx_lib
	  ../../scripts/fetch-ace.sh
	  mkdir static_libs
	  cp `g++ -print-file-name=libsupc++.a` static_libs
	  CXX=gcc CC=gcc cmake ../..
	  make
	  ldd bin/yarp  # should not contain libstdc++.so

2010-06-04  Paul Fitzpatrick  <paulfitz@alum.mit.edu>

	* src/carriers/tcpros_carrier/yarpros.cpp: small helper program
	for hooking up yarp ports and ROS entities, to the extent
	currently possible.

          yarpros roscore <hostname> <port number>
          -- tell yarp how to reach the ros master
          -- example: yarpros roscore 192.168.0.1 11311

          yarpros read <yarpname> <nodename> <topicname>
          -- read to a YARP port from a ROS node's contribution to a topic
          -- example: yarpros read /read /talker /chatter

          yarpros write <yarpname> <nodename> <topicname>
          -- write from a YARP port to a ROS node's subscription to a topic
          -- example: yarpros write /write /listener /chatter

          yarpros rpc <yarpname> <nodename> <servicename>
          -- write/read from a YARP port to a ROS node's named service
          -- example: yarpros rpc /rpc /add_two_ints_server /add_two_ints

	When using yarp read/write/rpc in combination with these,
	remember to use blob format for messages, since there is
	no type information yet.  E.G.
           [terminal 1] yarp rpc --client /rpc
	   [terminal 2] yarpros rpc /rpc /add_two_ints_server /add_two_ints
	   [terminal 1, type] {8 0 0 0 0 0 0 0   4 0 0 0 0 0 0 0}
	   [terminal 1, see]  {12 0 0 0 0 0 0 0}
	here you are reading/writing 64-bit integers by hand :-)
	
	* src/carriers/tcpros_carrier/TcpRosCarrier.cpp: implemented
	rudimentary writing to ROS subscribers, and writing to ROS
	services.  Be sure to read src/carriers/tcpros_carrier/README.TXT
	if you are tempted to play, this is not user-friendly stuff yet.

2010-06-03  Paul Fitzpatrick  <paulfitz@alum.mit.edu>

	* src/carriers/tcpros_carrier/CMakeLists.txt: implemented
	rudimentary (untyped) reading from ROS publishers.  Be sure
	to read src/carriers/tcpros_carrier/README.TXT if you are 
	tempted to play, this is not user-friendly stuff yet.

	* src/tests/CMakeLists.txt: freshen generation of device
	invocation examples - [thanks Andrew Stout]!

2010-06-03  Paul Fitzpatrick  <paulfitz@nominal.csail.mit.edu>

	* src/carriers/mjpeg_carrier/MjpegCarrier.cpp: add basic
	error recovery from unparsable jpegs.

2010-06-02  Paul Fitzpatrick  <paulfitz@alum.mit.edu>

	* src/carriers/mjpeg_carrier/MjpegCarrier.h: first pass at
	a carrier for reading writing images over mjpeg-over-http.
	Optional plugin, you need to select it in CMake.
	Works enough to read from mjpeg_streamer, and stream to
	supporting browsers (mozilla etc).  Example 1: if mjpeg_streamer
	is serving on port 8080, do:
	  yarp name register /streamer tcp ... 8080
	then:
	  yarpview /view
	then:
	  yarp connect /view /streamer mjpeg
	CAREFUL! The connect order is reversed to what you might expect
	because this is a "pull" protocol rather than a "push" protocol.
	Example 2: if "yarpdev --device test_grabber --name /grabber" is
	serving images you'd like to see in a browser, do:
	  yarp name query /grabber
	get the IP and port number, e.g. 127.0.0.1 and 10012, then in
	your browser visit something like:
	  http://127.0.0.1:10012/?action=stream
	[Thanks Philipp Robbel] for suggesting better mjpeg support.

2010-05-31  Ugo Pattacini  <ugo.pattacini@iit.it>

	* src/libYARP_OS/include/yarp/os/Network.h: Companion::exists()
    exported up to NetworkBase class level. 

2010-05-29  Paul Fitzpatrick  <paulfitz@alum.mit.edu>

	* src/libYARP_dev/src/ServerControlBoard.cpp: add 
	stream_state option to turn on/off streaming of encoder 
	state for default controlboard network wrapper.  E.g.:
	  yarpdev --device test_motor --stream_state 0
	(Do yarpdev --device test_motor --verbose for details.)
	[Thanks Ze Ji] for the suggestion.

2010-05-27  Paul Fitzpatrick  <paulfitz@alum.mit.edu>

	* src/carriers/xmlrpc_carrier/XmlRpcCarrier.h: basic XML/RPC
	carrier.  Experimental, but already sufficient to interoperate
	with the XmlRpc++ library's "Hello" server and client.  Not
	intended for high bandwidth uses.  Carrier name is "xmlrpc".
	XML structures are converted to Bottle-compatible form.
	Here's a quick test against ROS, which uses XML/RPC for some 
	APIs. Assumes roscore and "talker.cpp" tutorial example running:
	  yarp name register /roscore tcp localhost 11311
	  echo "lookupNode dummy_id /talker" | yarp rpc xmlrpc://roscore
            >> prints: 1 "node api" "http://contact:37291/"
	  yarp name register /talker tcp localhost 37291
	  echo "requestTopic dummy_id /chatter ((TCPROS))" | yarp rpc xmlrpc://talker
	    >> prints: 1 "" (TCPROS contact 38265)
	  yarp name register /talker/chatter tcp localhost 38265
	At that point we stop since port number 38265 talks the TCPROS 
	protocol, rather than XMLRPC.
	
	* src/libYARP_OS/include/yarp/os/Event.h: add wrapper
	for ACE_Event class.

2010-05-26  Paul Fitzpatrick  <paulfitz@alum.mit.edu>

	* src/libYARP_OS/src/PortWriterBuffer.cpp: correct counting
	mistake when recycling unwritten objects.  [Thanks Ugo Pattacini]!

2010-05-23  Paul Fitzpatrick  <paulfitz@alum.mit.edu>

	* src/libYARP_OS/include/yarp/os/BufferedPort.h: added
	unprepare method for situation where an object is prepared
	for writing, and then user decides not to write after all.
	Also improved default behavior in this case.

2010-05-17 Daniel Krieg  <krieg@fias.uni-frankfurt.de>

    * src/carriers/mpi_carrier/src/MpiStream.cpp: fixed thread
    problem -> now requesting MPI_THREAD_MULTIPLE level. Regarding
    OpenMPI faq thread support not intensively tested; I would recommend
    MPICH2 as mpi implementation.
    Preventing Mpi now from busy polling via non-blocking communcation.

2010-05-16  Paul Fitzpatrick  <paulfitz@alum.mit.edu>

	* example/swig/yarp.i: deal with conflict in PolyDriver::open
	variants when translated to python.

2010-05-14  Paul Fitzpatrick  <paulfitz@alum.mit.edu>

	* src/doc/yarp_config_files.dox: update config file documentation
	to include [include category_name section_name "filename.ini"]
	syntax.

	* src/libYARP_OS/src/Property.cpp: allow usage of 
	[include category_name section_name "filename.ini"] in
	configuration files.  This acts as if the material in
	"filename.ini" was included in a section called
	[category_name section_name]

