2009-11-13  Paul Fitzpatrick  <paulfitz@alum.mit.edu>

	* example/math/benchmark.cpp: Added math benchmark -
	[Thanks Arjan Gijsberts]

2009-11-12  Paul Fitzpatrick  <paulfitz@alum.mit.edu>

	* conf/CMakeLists.txt: start recording flags and options in
	header files, rather than just in YARPConfig.cmake.  This 
	makes those options easier to access without using cmake.
	Header files are created as yarp/conf/(version|options|system).h 
	initially in the include subdirectory of the binary directory.

2009-11-10  Paul Fitzpatrick  <paulfitz@alum.mit.edu>

	* src/libYARP_OS/harness/PropertyTest.cpp: add regression test
	for windows paths in environment variables.

	* src/libYARP_OS/src/Property.cpp: make exception for treatment
	of "\" characters in environment variables, to allow windows
	paths to work - [thanks David Vernon]!

2009-11-09  Paul Fitzpatrick  <paulfitz@alum.mit.edu>

	* src/CMakeLists.txt: remove YARP1 compatibility libraries
	as a build option.

	* example/swig/yarp.i: apply C# support patch from Stephane -
	[thanks Stephane Lallee]!  Also added better translation of
	the reply method.
	

2009-11-04  Paul Fitzpatrick  <paulfitz@alum.mit.edu>

	* src/libYARP_OS/src/PortCore.cpp: start enforcing some RPC
	contraints.  These only apply to users of the 
	RpcServer/RpcClient classes.

	* src/libYARP_OS/include/yarp/os/RpcServer.h: add a stub for 
	an RPC client specialization of Ports.  This adds no new 
	behavior, except to let the user declare that a port should
	only be used as an RPC client.  This will let YARP give better
	warnings/errors.

	* src/libYARP_OS/include/yarp/os/RpcClient.h: add a stub for 
	an RPC client specialization of Ports.  This adds no new 
	behavior, except to let the user declare that a port should
	only be used as an RPC client.  This will let YARP give better
	warnings/errors.

	* src/libYARP_OS/include/yarp/os/Port.h: add flags for tagging
	ports as input, output, and rpc based.

	* src/libYARP_OS/include/yarp/os/Property.h: make hash size
	of property objects configurable.

2009-10-29  Paul Fitzpatrick  <paulfitz@alum.mit.edu>

	* src/libYARP_OS/harness/PropertyTest.cpp
	* src/libYARP_sig/src/Image.cpp
	* src/libYARP_sig/src/ImageFile.cpp: deal with const char *
	conversions.

2009-10-28  Paul Fitzpatrick  <paulfitz@alum.mit.edu>

	* src/libYARP_OS/include/yarp/os/impl/Protocol.h: propagate
	carrier modifiers.  Carrier modifiers are not used yet,
	but will be convenient for accessing variants of standard
	port output.

2009-10-28  Arjan Gijsberts  <arjan@liralab.it>
	* src/libYARP_OS/src/BottleImpl.cpp
	* src/libYARP_sig/src/Vector.cpp
	* src/libYARP_sig/src/Matrix.cpp
	Increased buffers to 512 bytes to prevent buffer overflows when 
	printing (large) floating point numbers.

2009-10-27  Paul Fitzpatrick  <paulfitz@alum.mit.edu>

	* src/libYARP_OS/src/Companion.cpp: added rpcserver command:
	  yarp rpcserver /rpc/server/name
	This makes a trivial rpc server that is useful for testing.
	It waits for messages, and then replies with whatever you
	type on the console.

	* src/libYARP_OS/src/Companion.cpp: add "admin" option for
	using the port administrative interface.  So:
	  yarp admin rpc /port/name
	will now send administrative rather than data messages to 
	that port.  To get a list of administrative commands, type:
	  help
	while running "yarp admin rpc /port/name".  The admin
	option also works for:
	  yarp admin write /write/name /target/name

	* src/libYARP_OS/src/PortCore.cpp: add option for storing and
	forwarding RPC methods for debugging.  This is controlled by
	Port::setAutoOutputMode.  If set, then RPC transactions on
	input ports will be written to any connected output forms
	in Bottle-compatible form:
	  [rpc] (<input message>) (<reply message>)

2009-10-21  Paul Fitzpatrick  <paulfitz@alum.mit.edu>

	* src/libYARP_dev/src/ServerControlBoard.cpp: add explicit
	port interrupts when closing the device, in case there is
	a slow blocked transaction.

2009-10-18  Paul Fitzpatrick  <paulfitz@alum.mit.edu>

	* src/libYARP_OS/src/Bottle.cpp: give user a way to tag Bottles
	as modified externally (so serialization can happen correctly).

	* src/libYARP_OS/harness/BottleTest.cpp: add regression test
	for Value assignment operator.

	* src/libYARP_OS/src/Value.cpp: make Value assignment operator
	work as expected [thanks Philipp Robbel]

2009-10-16  Paul Fitzpatrick  <paulfitz@alum.mit.edu>

	* src/libYARP_OS/src/NameClient.cpp: remove dependency on
	"localhost" being correctly set - this leads to hard to debug
	problems if it is not set.  You still need the loopback device 
	though ([thanks Andrew Stout] and [thanks Baris Akgun] for 
	64-bit Ubuntu 9.04 reports).

