2009-04-29  Paul Fitzpatrick  <paulfitz@alum.mit.edu>

	* src/libYARP_OS/src/PortCore.cpp: bugfix: when closing
	a port, and shutting down connections, deal correctly with
	disconnections that fail because the port on the other 
	side no longer exists.  

	* src/libYARP_OS/src/PortCoreInputUnit.cpp: bugfix: when
	"success" flag of a read was clobbered (see below), the port 
	would fail to correctly move on to the next payload.

	* src/libYARP_OS/src/Port.cpp: bugfix: "success" flag of a 
	read could get clobbered by competing RPC calls.

